{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=goon|がち}}

{{IPAchar|/ɡʷat͡ɕi/}} → {{IPAchar|/ɡat͡ɕi/}}

First attested in the {{w|Edo period}}.

Appears to be a [[poetic]] use of the ''{{ll|ja|呉音|goon}}'' reading, in reference to a [[rank]] of {{m|ja|端女郎||tr=hashi jorō|low-end [[prostitute]]}} in the {{w|Kansai}} region. According to a popular song, a ''gachi'' prostitute cost one {{m|ja|匁||tr=monme|pos=old unit of [[currency]], worth roughly 3.75 [[gram]]s of [[silver]]}}, a {{m|ja|影||tr=kage|lit=[[shadow]]}} prostitute cost two ''monme'', and a {{m|ja|汐||tr=shio|lit=[[tide]]; [[loveliness]]}} prostitute cost three ''monme''.<ref name="DJR"/><ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref>

